1. About this software:
	MSYS Here is a loader for an MSYS environment.
	
2. Installation:
	"cd" to .\lib and build getopt.
	"cd" to .\winui\src and build the GUI library.
	Then "cd" to .\src and build MSYS Here.
	
	Copy msys.exe where your MSYS environment
	lives, eg: "C:\Msys\1.0".
	
	Modify MSYS path in .\setup\explorer.reg, eg:
	
	[HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\Directory\shell\MsysHere\command]
	@="C:\\Msys\\1.0\\msys.exe -h \"%1\""

	Double-click the reg file to import data into Windows registry.
	You should get a "MSYS Here" menu when right-clicking a
	drive/directory from Windows Explorer.
	
3. Thanks:
	MSYS Here uses the Cygwin version of getopt.
	Thanks to Christopher Faylor.
	